    "body": "Some changes requested\ngenerally speaking, when trying to match / improve the codebase:\n\n1. Repeated code is often an unrolled forloop\n2. Pointer math is bad (stuff like `(u8*), \"base + offset\", \"base + offset + index * index_offset\"`, etc. are bad and should be replcaed by struct indices, `obj->field` and `obj->field_arr[i]`\n3. pragmas usually aren't the ideal way to do things, mostly because that's probably not how they wrote it originally\n4. anytime you see \"jobj.h\", it's usually something done in jobj.h that's being inlined\n\nThese things are usually not 100% required, but for the functions you're already touching and you're using AI, might as well ask the AI to clean these up. Will document these points on the wiki as well for you",
